  <h1>
   date_days_in_month
  </h1>
  With this function you can get the number of days that the given month has, either 28, 29, 30 or 31.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">date_days_in_month(date);
</code></pre>
  <table>
   <tbody>
    <tr>
     <th>
      Argument
     </th>
     <th>
      Type
     </th>
     <th>
      Description
     </th>
    </tr>
    <tr>
     <td>
      date
     </td>
     <td>
      <span>
       <a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Maths_And_Numbers/Date_And_Time/date_current_datetime.htm">
        Datetime
       </a>
      </span>
     </td>
     <td>
      The date to use.
     </td>
    </tr>
   </tbody>
  </table>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">days = date_days_in_month(date_current_datetime());
</code></pre>
  This would set "days" to the number of days in the current month.
 </body>
